snippet.textDisplay: Lets be honest. The lyrics + the tune + the vocals were absolutely brilliant. These sisters have a great career ahead if used wisely. However, I was supposed to get goose bumps and was meant to be transcended into another world. Didn't happen. You know why? The music was totally rubbish and failed to uphold the magic. Apart from that violin synchronisation in the beginning which was breath taking, the rest was more like a rock ballad. Just ponder, do bulleh shah + nooran sisters + tune really require such appalling instrumental support. All that was needed was a subtle sub-continental instrumental fused with a hint of western  influence. FIND SOME REAL COMPOSERS. You are ruining the potentially amazing compositions.
snippet.textOriginal: Lets be honest. The lyrics + the tune + the vocals were absolutely brilliant. These sisters have a great career ahead if used wisely.
